Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and onion to the ovenproof pan and
stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir through the @Risotto Rice{175%g},
garlic and @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are
translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Boiled Water for the Risotto{600%ml} and @Vegetable Stock Paste{20%g}.
Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has
been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no
> pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways. Chop into
1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the
courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple
of mins.

While the courgette is frying, zest and cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges.

Transfer your charred courgette into a #medium-sized bowl{}, add a good squeeze
of lemon, lemon zest and the @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the
dressing.

Season and set aside to marinate.

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @Asparagus{100%g}(trimmed) and discard. Chop into
thirds.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the now-empty frying pan on medium heat.

Once hot, add the asparagus and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.
Fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of water and immediately cover with a lid
or some foil.

Cook until the asparagus is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the
@Pesto{32%g}, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g} and @Butter{20%g}.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Stir through the marinated courgette.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and lemon juice if you feel it needs it.

Share your risotto between your serving plates.

Scatter the asparagus on top of your risotto to finish. Enjoy!